India's biggest weakness is rampant Corruption and Chaos..and the biggest reason for the growth of all Corruptions and Crime is our country's lax.. stagnant.. biased.. Judiciary System based on British-era's crooked hermad Laws which is moved and directed by money ghouls unscrupulous Lawyers , self-righteous, shameless Judiciary ; being the most populous country in the world, such a law and justice system in INDIA is  nothing but anathema ; When people go to the door of the court to seek Justice for an unjust Crime, they first have to go to the money ghoul Lawyer. The torture of the court will start after the trial candidate's case starts.. The Court will be continuing sprinkling salt on their cut of  wounds.. giving date after date.. make them  waiting for the trial and final Judgement forever.. when will it the end, the naive trial candidate, the justice seeker does not know.. the case maybe pending for 10 - 20 - 30 years. .. or will continue longer, no one knows in this India ; The lamp of many Justice Seekers lives are extinguished, many have no more time to listen to the words of Judgment ; On the other hand, famous Criminals appoint expensive Lawyers, who are experts in the field of weaving a web of lies, who are always ready to find out the intricate immaginatory ways to prove their criminal Clients INNOCENT or reduce the sentence so that they can get Bail immediately ;
As a result, Nowadays most of the crime prone people become extremely confident. .. The common man's trust in law and order is decreasing day by day.. which is slowly leading our country to Hell ; At this moment few Crores of cases are pending in different courts of the country.. which is a World record ;
All small and big developed countries of the world are wrapped in strict rule of Law,  people of these countries are forced to follow all good  rules and regulations of a responsible citizen.. so when we walk on the streets of Dubai or Tokyo or London.. we are forced to think many times, should we throw a piece of small polythene or even a piece of cigarette butt on the street or not !! On the other hand,
in our country people never hesitate to spit on the walls of government office stairs !! One example is enough to understand the whole difference between India  and advanced world.. as well as true law and order situation of this largest democracy .

